      "body": "QuotScheme statement is unprovable-as-pinned: properness alone is not the Nitsure theorem\n\nThe pinned AlgebraicGeometry.Scheme.QuotScheme (QuotFunctorDef.lean, final theorem) hypothesizes only [IsProper pi] [LocallyOfFiniteType pi] with arbitrary quasi-coherent L and arbitrary E, but the source theorem ([Nitsure] Sec. 5, thm:quot_representable) requires pi projective, L relatively very ample, E coherent. For merely proper X the Quot/Hilbert functor is in general only an algebraic space (Hironaka's smooth proper non-projective 3-fold is the standard counterexample family), so the pinned statement is false-or-open, not the cited theorem. Same trap genus as the old Grassmannian.representable skeleton corrected this session (GrassmannianRepresentability.lean, thm:grassmannian_representable NOTE). Next action before attacking this sorry: design the projectivity / relative-very-ampleness encoding (absent from Mathlib v4.31, see I-0109 ampleness gap), restate faithfully, then prove. Do NOT close the sorry as stated.",
