          "item": "I-0118",
          "author": "ground",
          "at": "2026-07-05T13:10:43.295991+00:00",
          "body": "**Blueprint side reconciled (session 0109-ground).** The node `thm:quot_representable` (`Picard_QuotScheme.tex:4374`) was marked `\\leanok` despite (a) its Lean target `QuotScheme` being an unproved `sorry` and (b) the statement mismatch you flag. I set it to `\\notready` with an inline comment recording the mismatch, so the DAG no longer claims the weak/false Lean signature is verified.\n\n- The **blueprint statement is correct** (projective $\\pi$, relatively very ample $L$, coherent $E$ \u2014 matches Nitsure \u00a75). The defect is purely on the Lean side: `QuotScheme` hypothesizes only `[IsProper] [LocallyOfFiniteType]` over arbitrary quasi-coherent $L,E$.\n- Per memory `I-0074` caveat 2, Mathlib v4.31 has no projectivity/very-ampleness vocabulary, so the Lean cannot yet be restated to match \u2014 the honest move is to leave `QuotScheme` unproved (or re-scope it) rather than prove the false pinned form."
        },
        {
          "id": "C-0002",
          "item": "I-0118",
          "author": "human",
          "at": "2026-07-06T02:11:51.287996+00:00",
          "body": "**Restatement design settled** (T12 ultracode session triage; Mathlib v4.31 vocabulary hunt done \u2014 NO IsProjective/QuasiProjective morphism class, NO VeryAmple/IsAmple for sheaves, NO relative Proj or $\\mathbb{P}^n_S$, NO $\\mathcal{O}(1)$ as a sheaf of modules anywhere in Mathlib).\n\nRecommended faithful encoding (a): build the missing vocabulary block project-side \u2014\n- $\\mathbb{P}(n;S) :=$ `pullback (terminal.from S) (terminal.from (Proj (MvPolynomial.homogeneousSubmodule (Fin n) \u2124)))`, in the style of Mathlib's `AffineSpace` (`AffineSpace.lean:44`). Properness of the structural map comes from Mathlib's `IsProper (Proj.toSpecZero \ud835\udc9c)` (`ProjectiveSpectrum/Proper.lean:368`) + base change.\n- Serre twist $\\mathcal{O}(1)$ as a `SheafOfModules` on `Proj \ud835\udc9c`, glued over the `away\u03b9`/basic-open affine cover with transitions $t_i/t_j$ \u2014 the project's `GlueDescent`/`GrassmannianZariskiSheaf` module-gluing engine is the substrate.\n- Then restate: `theorem QuotScheme \u2026 (hE : E.IsFinitePresentation) (emb : \u2203 n (i : X \u27f6 \u2119(n;S)), IsClosedImmersion i \u2227 i \u226b proj = \u03c0 \u2227 Nonempty (L \u2245 i^* \ud835\udcaa(1)))` and flip `thm:quot_representable` from \\notready.\n\nFallback encoding (c) for the sole Route-A consumer ($S = \\operatorname{Spec} k$): very-ampleness through the project's own `SectionGradedRing` $\\bigoplus_m \\Gamma(X, L^{\\otimes m})$ + Mathlib `Proj.fromOfGlobalSections` (`ProjectiveSpectrum/Basic.lean:439`): hypothesis = the canonical $X \\to \\operatorname{Proj}$ of the section ring is a closed immersion + degree-1 generation/finite type.\n\nEncoding (b) (a class packaging the Nitsure-consumed consequences \u2014 m-regularity bounds, pushforward local freeness) is REJECTED as the public statement: conclusion-carrier of the `HasSmoothProperQuotient` genus, statement-drift magnet; acceptable only as a use-site hypothesis.\n\nNext action: dedicated vocabulary-build session for $\\mathbb{P}(n;S)$ + $\\mathcal{O}(1)$, then the restatement. Until then `Scheme.QuotScheme` (QuotFunctorDef.lean:753) keeps its sorry."
        },
        {
          "id": "C-0003",
          "item": "I-0118",
          "author": "ground",
          "at": "2026-07-06T07:13:11.155210+00:00",
          "body": "**Projectivity vocabulary for the honest restatement now exists (T14, run 0014).**\n\n- `Picard/ProjectiveMorphism.lean` defines `Scheme.Hom.IsProjectiveWith \u03c0 L` \u2014 a closed immersion into `\u2119(Fin(d+1);S)` over `S` with `L \u2245 i^*O(1)` \u2014 the encoding (a) settled on this issue. `isProper`/`comp_isClosedImmersion`/`baseChange` are fully proved.\n- `SerreFiniteness.lean` states `sectionGradedModule_fg` under `IsProjectiveWith` (very ample + coherent), i.e. the strong true Serre statement, **not** the proper-only trap this issue warns about.\n- The `QuotScheme` final theorem in `QuotFunctorDef.lean` is still pinned with `[IsProper \u03c0] [LocallyOfFiniteType \u03c0]` only \u2014 unchanged, still false-as-pinned. The restatement consuming `IsProjectiveWith` (specialised to `Scheme.{0}`, since the glue engine is universe-monomorphic) remains open.\n\nKeeping open: the substrate is ready but the restatement itself is not yet done."
        },
        {
          "id": "C-0004",
