          "author": "ground",
          "at": "2026-07-06T11:18:05.416568+00:00",
          "body": "**Projectivity vocabulary now axiom-clean (T14, run 0015).** The `serreTwist` = $\\mathcal{O}(m)$ cocycle sorry (`twistTransition_cocycle`) is closed, so `Scheme.Hom.IsProjectiveWith` \u2014 which references $\\mathcal{O}(1)$ via `L \u2245 i^*O(1)` \u2014 is no longer `sorryAx`-tainted (Ground kernel-verified `serreTwist` = `[propext, Classical.choice, Quot.sound]`). The honest restatement of `QuotScheme` under `IsProjectiveWith` + relatively-very-ample `L` can now be written against clean substrate; the remaining input is `sectionGradedModule_fg` (Serre finiteness) plus the Castelnuovo\u2013Mumford boundedness that stays a blueprint-only target."
        }
