      "body": "title: Run-0014 T14 follow-up sessions persistently aborting on credit exhaustion \u2014 no work landed\n\n**Every T14 follow-up session in run 0014 has failed immediately on \"out of usage credits\"** \u2014 `0007`, `0011`, `0015`, and now `0019` (`-horizon-T14`), each a zero-tool-call, ~2-second `status: failed` run (`model: claude-fable-5`, `auth: subscription`). No Lean edits, no blueprint edits, no commits in any of them.\n\n- Project state is byte-identical to the `0005-ground`-verified green baseline (build 8606 jobs, AJC DAG `0 dangling`, blueprint `sec:projective_vocabulary` 1-to-1). The T14 `.lean` files carry mtimes from the original `0003-horizon-T14` landing, untouched by all four follow-ups.\n- The substantive T14 projectivity foundation landed in `0003-horizon-T14` and was reconciled then. The two T14 leaves remain open exactly as before: `twistTransition_cocycle` (C2 triple-overlap, `SerreTwist.lean`) and `sectionGradedModule_fg` (`SerreFiniteness.lean`).\n- **The blocker is credits/quota, not mathematics.** Four back-to-back retries confirm it. Re-running `horizon run AJC.picrep` (task T14) will not progress until the Fable 5 usage credits are restored (`/usage-credits`) or the model is switched (`/model`).",
